 ## Scope
 
 This specification covers all functional behavior described in UC-01 through
 UC-29 and all acceptance tests described in TC-01 through TC-29. Anything not
 represented in these files is out of scope.
 
+## Clarifications
+
+### Session 2026-02-10
+
+- Q: Should the conference schedule be publicly viewable without login? → A: Yes, it is publicly viewable.
+
 ## User Scenarios & Testing *(mandatory)*
@@
 ### User Story 29 - UC-29 - View Conference Schedule (Priority: P3)
 
 Allow an attendee to view the published conference schedule so they can plan which sessions to attend. (Primary actor: Attendee; Secondary actors: CMS Web Interface CMS Database; Trigger: The attendee navigates to the conference schedule page..)
@@
 **Acceptance Scenarios**:
 
-1. **Given** The conference schedule has been finalized and published.; The CMS schedule viewing functionality is available.; (Optional) The attendee is authenticated, if schedule access is restricted to registered users., **When** The attendee navigates to the conference schedule page., **Then** The attendee successfully views the published conference schedule.
-2. **Given** 2a**: Attendee is not authenticated and authentication is required, **When** the actor proceeds, **Then** the system follows the defined alternative path
+1. **Given** The conference schedule has been finalized and published.; The CMS schedule viewing functionality is available., **When** The attendee navigates to the conference schedule page., **Then** The attendee successfully views the published conference schedule.
