2026-02-10T02:35:28.034077Z  INFO session_loop{thread_id=019c4531-58bd-7d10-8426-8dff35a256e1}: codex_core::stream_events_utils: ToolCall: exec_command {"cmd":"cat <<'EOF' > /home/mlai/ubuntu-blade/ubuntu/year5/ece493/Lab2/ece493-cms/specs/001-uc-spec-union/checklists/scenario.md\n# Scenario Coverage Checklist: UC-Driven Specification & Unified UAT\n\n**Purpose**: Validate scenario coverage and requirement quality for UC/TC-derived specifications\n**Created**: 2026-02-10\n**Feature**: /home/mlai/ubuntu-blade/ubuntu/year5/ece493/Lab2/ece493-cms/specs/001-uc-spec-union/spec.md\n\n**Note**: This checklist is generated by the `/speckit.checklist` command based on feature context and requirements.\n\n## Requirement Completeness\n\n- [ ] CHK001 Are all UC-XX elements represented for each user story? [Completeness, Spec §User Scenarios & Testing]\n- [ ] CHK002 Are all TC-XX acceptance tests referenced by the UAT index requirement? [Completeness, Spec §User Acceptance Tests]\n- [ ] CHK003 Are out-of-scope boundaries explicitly stated for items not in UC/TC? [Completeness, Spec §Scope]\n- [ ] CHK004 Are all entities listed under Key Entities tied to at least one requirement or user story? [Completeness, Spec §Key Entities, Spec §Requirements]\n- [ ] CHK005 Are role-based access requirements stated for every role mentioned in UC-XX? [Completeness, Spec §Security & Privacy Considerations, Spec §User Scenarios & Testing]\n\n## Requirement Clarity\n\n- [ ] CHK006 Is public schedule access unambiguous about required authentication? [Clarity, Spec §Clarifications, Spec §User Story 29]\n- [ ] CHK007 Are triggers described clearly enough to distinguish actor-initiated vs system-initiated flows? [Clarity, Spec §User Scenarios & Testing]\n- [ ] CHK008 Are priority rationales explicitly stated for each user story? [Clarity, Spec §User Scenarios & Testing]\n- [ ] CHK009 Are independent tests phrased as measurable outcomes rather than broad statements? [Clarity, Spec §User Scenarios & Testing]\n- [ ] CHK010 Is the UAT index content requirement specific to test case IDs and titles only? [Clarity, Spec §User Acceptance Tests, Spec §Clarifications]\n\n## Requirement Consistency\n\n- [ ] CHK011 Are role terms consistent (Referee vs Reviewer) across all sections? [Consistency, Spec §Terminology, Spec §Security & Privacy Considerations, Spec §User Scenarios & Testing]\n- [ ] CHK012 Do edge cases align with acceptance scenarios for the same UC? [Consistency, Spec §Edge Cases, Spec §User Scenarios & Testing]\n- [ ] CHK013 Do functional requirements map one-to-one with user stories and UC IDs? [Consistency, Spec §Requirements, Spec §Use Case Coverage]\n- [ ] CHK014 Is public schedule access consistent between UC-03 and UC-29? [Consistency, Spec §User Story 3, Spec §User Story 29]\n- [ ] CHK015 Are security/privacy statements consistent with public-access scenarios? [Consistency, Spec §Security & Privacy Considerations, Spec §User Stories 1-3, Spec §User Story 29]\n\n## Acceptance Criteria Quality\n\n- [ ] CHK016 Are success criteria measurable and tied to UC/TC coverage? [Acceptance Criteria, Spec §Success Criteria]\n- [ ] CHK017 Are acceptance scenarios present for every user story? [Acceptance Criteria, Spec §User Scenarios & Testing]\n- [ ] CHK018 Are independent tests traceable to acceptance scenarios for each story? [Acceptance Criteria, Spec §User Scenarios & Testing]\n- [ ] CHK019 Is the UAT pass condition explicitly defined for release readiness? [Measurability, Spec §Success Criteria, Spec §User Acceptance Tests]\n\n## Scenario Coverage\n\n- [ ] CHK020 Are alternate flows from UC extensions captured in acceptance scenarios for each use case? [Coverage, Spec §User Scenarios & Testing]\n- [ ] CHK021 Are exception/error scenarios for authentication, payment declines, and missing data explicitly specified? [Coverage, Spec §Edge Cases]\n- [ ] CHK022 Are recovery requirements defined after notification delivery failures? [Gap, Spec §Edge Cases]\n- [ ] CHK023 Are save/resume submission scenarios fully specified (state after partial save, resume behavior)? [Coverage, Spec §User Story 10]\n- [ ] CHK024 Are schedule generation/edit/publish flows covered across admin/editor roles without gaps? [Coverage, Spec §User Stories 22-25]\n\n## Edge Case Coverage\n\n- [ ] CHK025 Are zero-state scenarios (no announcements, no assigned papers, no published schedule) defined? [Edge Case, Spec §Edge Cases]\n- [ ] CHK026 Are invalid input formats (email, manuscript file) handled with explicit requirements? [Edge Case, Spec §Edge Cases]\n- [ ] CHK027 Are concurrency/conflict cases (simultaneous schedule edits, reviewer workload limit) specified? [Gap, Spec §User Stories 17, 22, 24]\n- [ ] CHK028 Are data availability failures (missing scheduling data) specified with outcomes? [Edge Case, Spec §Edge Cases]\n\n## Non-Functional Requirements\n\n- [ ] CHK029 Are performance goals tied to specific user journeys rather than generic statements? [Clarity, Plan §Technical Context]\n- [ ] CHK030 Are audit logging requirements explicitly listed for critical actions? [Completeness, Spec §Security & Privacy Considerations]\n- [ ] CHK031 Are privacy requirements defined beyond classification (e.g., access limits, retention)? [Gap, Spec §Security & Privacy Considerations, Spec §Dependencies]\n\n## Dependencies & Assumptions\n\n- [ ] CHK032 Are dependencies on UC/TC files documented with ownership or versioning expectations? [Assumption, Spec §Dependencies]\n- [ ] CHK033 Are external service requirements (payment, notification) defined for availability and failure handling? [Gap, Spec §User Stories 11, 12, 25, 27, 28]\n- [ ] CHK034 Are assumptions about public access and authentication explicitly recorded? [Assumption, Spec §Clarifications, Spec §Assumptions]\n\n## Ambiguities & Conflicts\n\n- [ ] CHK035 Are terms like \"valid\", \"complete\", and \"secure\" defined with concrete criteria? [Ambiguity, Spec §User Story 5]\n- [ ] CHK036 Is the overlap between schedule viewing use cases (UC-03 vs UC-29) clearly reconciled? [Ambiguity, Spec §User Story 3, Spec §User Story 29]\n\n## Notes\n\n- Check items off as completed: `[x]`\n- Add comments or findings inline\n- Link to relevant resources or documentation\n- Items are numbered sequentially for easy reference\nEOF"} thread_id=019c4531-58bd-7d10-8426-8dff35a256e1
